The family of a Katsina born retired diplomat and prominent politician, Alhaji Musa Musawa, has said that he is alive and well. This is contrary to information trending in the media that he had passed on.
In a chat with LEADERSHIP.ng, his daughter, Ms Hannatu Musawa clarified that though her father was ill recently, he is not dead as being speculated in the media. She thanked relations and friends who have been inundating the family with inquiries for their concern. We recall that the Emir of Kano, Alhaji Muhammadu Sanusi visited the ailing elder statesmen at his hospital bed recently.